    public static final String Hos_12_3 = "He took his brother by the heel in the womb, and by his strength he had power with God: ";
    public static final String Hos_12_4 = "Yea, he had power over the angel, and prevailed: he wept, and made supplication unto him: he found him [in] Bethel, and there he spake with us; ";
    public static final String Hos_12_5 = "Even the LORD God of hosts; the LORD [is] his memorial. ";
    public static final String Hos_12_6 = "Therefore turn thou to thy God: keep mercy and judgment, and wait on thy God continually. ";
    public static final String Hos_12_7 = "[He is] a merchant, the balances of deceit [are] in his hand: he loveth to oppress. ";
    public static final String Hos_12_8 = "And Ephraim said, Yet I am become rich, I have found me out substance: [in] all my labours they shall find none iniquity in me that [were] sin. ";
    public static final String Hos_12_9 = "And I [that am] the LORD thy God from the land of Egypt will yet make thee to dwell in tabernacles, as in the days of the solemn feast. ";
    public static final String Hos_12_10 = "I have also spoken by the prophets, and I have multiplied visions, and used similitudes, by the ministry of the prophets. ";
    public static final String Hos_12_11 = "[Is there] iniquity [in] Gilead? surely they are vanity: they sacrifice bullocks in Gilgal; yea, their altars [are] as heaps in the furrows of the fields. ";
    public static final String Hos_12_12 = "And Jacob fled into the country of Syria, and Israel served for a wife, and for a wife he kept [sheep. ]";
    public static final String Hos_12_13 = "And by a prophet the LORD brought Israel out of Egypt, and by a prophet was he preserved. ";
    public static final String Hos_12_14 = "Ephraim provoked [him] to anger most bitterly: therefore shall he leave his blood upon him, and his reproach shall his Lord return unto him. ";
    public static final String Hos_13_1 = "When Ephraim spake trembling, he exalted himself in Israel; but when he offended in Baal, he died. ";
    public static final String Hos_13_2 = "And now they sin more and more, and have made them molten images of their silver, [and] idols according to their own understanding, all of it the work of the craftsmen: they say of them, Let the men that sacrifice kiss the calves. ";
    public static final String Hos_13_3 = "Therefore they shall be as the morning cloud, and as the early dew that passeth away, as the chaff [that] is driven with the whirlwind out of the floor, and as the smoke out of the chimney. ";
    public static final String Hos_13_4 = "Yet I [am] the LORD thy God from the land of Egypt, and thou shalt know no god but me: for [there is] no saviour beside me. ";
    public static final String Hos_13_5 = "I did know thee in the wilderness, in the land of great drought. ";
    public static final String Hos_13_6 = "According to their pasture, so were they filled; they were filled, and their heart was exalted; therefore have they forgotten me. ";
    public static final String Hos_13_7 = "Therefore I will be unto them as a lion: as a leopard by the way will I observe [them: ]";
    public static final String Hos_13_8 = "I will meet them as a bear [that is] bereaved [of her whelps,] and will rend the caul of their heart, and there will I devour them like a lion: the wild beast shall tear them. ";
    public static final String Hos_13_9 = "O Israel, thou hast destroyed thyself; but in me [is] thine help. ";
    public static final String Hos_13_10 = "I will be thy king: where [is any other] that may save thee in all thy cities? and thy judges of whom thou saidst, Give me a king and princes? ";
    public static final String Hos_13_11 = "I gave thee a king in mine anger, and took [him] away in my wrath. ";
    public static final String Hos_13_12 = "The iniquity of Ephraim [is] bound up; his sin [is] hid. ";
    public static final String Hos_13_13 = "The sorrows of a travailing woman shall come upon him: he [is] an unwise son; for he should not stay long in [the place of] the breaking forth of children. ";
    public static final String Hos_13_14 = "I will ransom them from the power of the grave; I will redeem them from death: O death, I will be thy plagues; O grave, I will be thy destruction: repentance shall be hid from mine eyes. ";
    public static final String Hos_13_15 = "Though he be fruitful among [his] brethren, an east wind shall come, the wind of the LORD shall come up from the wilderness, and his spring shall become dry, and his fountain shall be dried up: he shall spoil the treasure of all pleasant vessels. ";
    public static final String Hos_13_16 = "Samaria shall become desolate; for she hath rebelled against her God: they shall fall by the sword: their infants shall be dashed in pieces, and their women with child shall be ripped up. ";
    public static final String Hos_14_1 = "O Israel, return unto the LORD thy God; for thou hast fallen by thine iniquity. ";
    public static final String Hos_14_2 = "Take with you words, and turn to the LORD: say unto him, Take away all iniquity, and receive [us] graciously: so will we render the calves of our lips. ";
    public static final String Hos_14_3 = "Asshur shall not save us; we will not ride upon horses: neither will we say any more to the work of our hands, [Ye are] our gods: for in thee the fatherless findeth mercy. ";
    public static final String Hos_14_4 = "I will heal their backsliding, I will love them freely: for mine anger is turned away from him. ";
    public static final String Hos_14_5 = "I will be as the dew unto Israel: he shall grow as the lily, and cast forth his roots as Lebanon. ";
    public static final String Hos_14_6 = "His branches shall spread, and his beauty shall be as the olive tree, and his smell as Lebanon. ";
    public static final String Hos_14_7 = "They that dwell under his shadow shall return; they shall revive [as] the corn, and grow as the vine: the scent thereof [shall be] as the wine of Lebanon. ";
    public static final String Hos_14_8 = "Ephraim [shall say,] What have I to do any more with idols? I have heard [him,] and observed him: I [am] like a green fir tree. From me is thy fruit found. ";
    public static final String Hos_14_9 = "Who [is] wise, and he shall understand these [things?] prudent, and he shall know them? for the ways of the LORD [are] right, and the just shall walk in them: but the transgressors shall fall therein. ";
